h3. Issue Summary

Unable to install/uninstall apps appropriately after migrating from Atlassian Cloud.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# [Migrate from Confluence Cloud to Server|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/migrate-from-confluence-cloud-to-server-298979321.html]
# Try to install app (e.g. Team Calendars)
# Try to uninstall the app

h3. Expected Results

The app can be installed/uninstalled without any problem.

h3. Actual Results

When you try to install Team Calendars, you will see the following error. (However, the app is actually installed.)

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

You will see the following error in {{atlassian-confluence.log}}.

{code:java}
2019-04-09 02:13:35,771 WARN [UpmAsynchronousTaskManager:thread-4] [rest.resources.install.InstallTask] run Unexpected error in install task
 -- url: /rest/plugins/1.0/ | referer: http://conf6151.localtest.me:8090/plugins/servlet/upm/marketplace/search?q=team%20cal | traceId: d84b6ea6362d50ff | userName: recovery_admin
java.lang.RuntimeException: Failed to parse AuditLogEntry from JSON string: {"userKey":"","accountId":"anonymous","date":1553834285704,"i18nKey":"upm.auditLog.install.plugin.success","entryType":"PLUGIN_INSTALL","params":["Jira Ops integration","jira-ops-confluence-integration","1.0.4-AC"]}
{code}

When you try to uninstall Team Calendars, the uninstallation seems to succeeded. However, if you restart Confluence instance, the app is still listed in _Manage apps_ page.

h3. Notes

This problem is caused by the data which is imported from Cloud.

{code:sql}
select bandanavalue FROM bandana WHERE bandanakey like 'com.atlassian.upm.log.PluginSettingsAuditLogService:log:upm_audit_log_v3';
{code}
{code}
<list>
  <string>{&quot;userKey&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;accountId&quot;:&quot;anonymous&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:1553834285704,&quot;i18nKey&quot;:&quot;upm.auditLog.install.plugin.success&quot;,&quot;entryType&quot;:&quot;PLUGIN_INSTALL&quot;,&quot;params&quot;:[&quot;Jira Ops integration&quot;,&quot;jira-ops-confluence-integration&quot;,&quot;1.0.4-AC&quot;]} 
 </string>
  ...
</list>
{code}

The strings are HTML escaped but they contained the following JSON data.

{code}
{"userKey":"","accountId":"anonymous","date":1553834285704,"i18nKey":"upm.auditLog.install.plugin.success","entryType":"PLUGIN_INSTALL","params":["Jira Ops integration","jira-ops-confluence-integration","1.0.4-AC"]}
{code}

A key "accountId" is only used in Confluence Cloud and it shouldn't exist in Confluence Server.

h3. Workaround

Please remove the key "accountId" from the problematic record with SQL below. (This SQL is tested on PostgreSQL.)

{code:sql}
update bandana set bandanavalue = replace(bandanavalue, ',&quot;accountId&quot;:&quot;anonymous&quot;', '') where bandanakey like 'com.atlassian.upm.log.PluginSettingsAuditLogService:log:upm_audit_log_v3';
{code}

If you've installed some apps on Confluence Cloud, you also need to execute the following SQL.

{code:sql}
update bandana set bandanavalue = replace(bandanavalue, ',&quot;accountId&quot;:&quot;Unknown user&quot;', '') where bandanakey like 'com.atlassian.upm.log.PluginSettingsAuditLogService:log:upm_audit_log_v3';
{code}

(i) Please make sure to take a backup before modifying the DB record.

h3. Problem Definition

Space admins are giving other individual users admin privileges within spaces they control. 
 Permissions in this environment are managed using an automated tool (AGS) and it is not desired to grant permissions to individual users on the root of the space without approval or potentially at all.
h3. Suggested Solution

The desired outcome is to allow the Global admin to restrict a Space admin's ability to grant the "admin" privilege of a space to individual users while still allowing the space admin to grant other permissions to individual users. 
 Stated differently, the desired ability is for the Global admin to remove the "admin" privilege as an option for Space admin's to select. The Global admin would be the only one who can grant admin privilege at the space-level 
h3. Why this is important

Global admins should have the ability to determine who can fill a space admin role, as individual space admins potentially give this right to users that should not have it.
 The unauthorized admins then have rights not controlled via automation.
h3. Workaround

As a workaround, the Confluence administrator can hide the UI elements that are used to assign/remove the Space Admin permissions in the Space Tools page.
 Note that this will not remove the functionality, but just hide the element so that users can't see these and, therefore, change its value.
 The elements will be hidden from all users, also applying to Confluence administrators.
 # Go to *Cog icon* > *General configuration* > *Stylesheet* to open the [_Global Stylesheet_|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/styling-confluence-with-css-166528400.html] admin page.
 # Click on the _Edit_ button, add the code below and then _Save_ it.
 ** You may use any combination of the following options to hide one or multiple elements.
{code:java}
/* Hide the checkbox of space admin permissions related to groups */
.permissions.aui input[name^=confluence_checkbox_setspacepermissions_group]  
{    
  visibility:hidden !important;
}

/* Hide the checkbox of space admin permissions related to users */
.permissions.aui input[name^=confluence_checkbox_setspacepermissions_user]  
{    
  visibility:hidden !important;    
}

/* Hide the checkbox of space admin permissions related to anonymous users */
.permissions.aui input[name^=confluence_checkbox_setspacepermissions_anonymous]  
{    
  visibility:hidden !important;    
}

/* Hide the button to check and uncheck all options in the permissions row */
.permissions.aui button.aui-button.aui-button-text.row-selector
{
	visibility:hidden !important;
}
{code}

(!) If anyone needs to set the Space Admin permissions, then the Confluence Admin must to remove this code from Confluence stylesheet.

h3. Issue Summary

Cloud Migration Assistant app shows up in the list of user installed apps even after being uninstalled from the UI
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Go to  !https://confluence.atlassian.com/support/files/790796813/947856965/1/1522298459209/cog-new.png|width=16!  ** > Manage Apps
 # Choose *User Installed* from the drop-down
# Uninstall Cloud Migration Assistant app, a message would pop-up stating the app has been uninstalled

 !Screen Shot 2019-04-05 at 12.16.42 PM.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Expected Results

Cloud Migration Assistant app is uninstalled completely
h3. Actual Results

After each restart Cloud Migration Assistant app shows up in the list again with the below

 !Screen Shot 2019-04-05 at 12.35.27 PM.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Notes

*  It would also throw the below error in the logs:
{code}
2019-03-26 17:04:43,015 ERROR [Caesium-1-3] [migration.agent.queue.QueueBroker] error An error occurred when getting the next batch for consumer type: CONFLUENCE_IMPORT. Message: org.hibernate.tool.schema.spi.SchemaManagementException: Schema-validation: missing column [scheduleDate] in table [MIG_PLAN]
com.atlassian.util.concurrent.LazyReference$InitializationException: org.hibernate.tool.schema.spi.SchemaManagementException: Schema-validation: missing column [scheduleDate] in table [MIG_PLAN]
        at com.atlassian.util.concurrent.LazyReference.getInterruptibly(LazyReference.java:149)
        at com.atlassian.util.concurrent.LazyReference.get(LazyReference.java:112)
{code}

* The only way to get around this log spam is to drop the tables associated with Migration Assistant and clear caches as per the [documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/confkb/how-to-clear-confluence-plugins-cache-297664846.html]:
{code}
drop table MIG_ANALYTICS_EVENT;
drop table MIG_ATTACHMENT;
drop table MIG_SEQUENCES;
drop table MIG_STATS;
drop table MIG_STEP;
drop table MIG_TASK;
drop table MIG_WORK_ITEM;
drop table MIG_PLAN;
drop table MIG_CLOUD_SITE;
drop table MIG_DB_CHANGELOG;
drop table MIG_DB_CHANGELOG_LOCK;
{code}

h3. Workaround

Currently, there is no known workaround wholistically as far as the UI is concerned but if we check the status of the app from the database you will notice that the app is actually uninstalled

*DB Query*
{code:sql}
select PLUGINDATAID, PLUGINKEY, FILENAME, LASTMODDATE from PLUGINDATA;
{code}

